017\n*[[J1 League]] Goal of the Year: [[2019 J1 League|2019]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.japantimes.co.jp/sports/2019/12/08/soccer/j-league/marinos-midfielder-teruhito-nakagawa-named-j-league-mvp-andres-iniesta-joins-marinos-tokyo-players-best-xi|title=Teruhito Nakagawa named J. League MVP, with Iniesta joining Marinos and Tokyo players in Best XI|publisher=The Japan Times|date=7 December 2019|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n'''Achievements'''\n*[[Valencia CF|Valencia]] Top Scorer: [[2005\u201306 La Liga|2005\u201306]], [[2006\u201307 La Liga|2006\u201307]], [[2007\u201308 La Liga|2007\u201308]], [[2008\u201309 La Liga|2008\u201309]], [[2009\u201310 La Liga|2009\u201310]]\n*[[La Liga]]'s Top Assisting Player: [[2006\u201307 La Liga|2006\u201307]]<ref name=\"sidvilla\" />\n*Spain all-time top scorer: [[Spain national football team records#Top goalscorers|59 goals]]\n*Spain's all-time top scorer in [[FIFA World Cup]] matches\n*[[New York City FC]] all-time top scorer: [[List of New York City FC records and statistics#Goalscorers|80 goals]]\n*Most goals scored in one [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] (by a Spanish international): 5\n*Most goals scored in one calendar year (by a Spanish international): 12 (2008, 2009)<ref name=\"marca ano natural\" />\n*Largest streak of games having scored (by a Spanish international): 6<ref name=\"Spain Hotshot David Villa Delighted\" />\n\n'''Decorations'''\n*[[Prince of Asturias Awards]]: 2010\n*[[Royal Order of Sports Merit|Gold Medal of the Royal Order of Sporting Merit]]: 2011<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.mundodeportivo.com/20111005/futbol/seleccion-espanola/las-campeones-del-mundo-de-futbol-ya-tienen-la-real-orden-del-merito-deportivo_54226408413.html |title=Las campeones del mundo de f\u00fatbol ya tienen la Real Orden del M\u00e9rito Deportivo |last=Bru\u00f1a |first=Manel |date=5 October 2011 |access-date=25 July 2013 |newspaper=[[Mundo Deportivo]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|David Villa}}\n{{portal|Biography|Association football|Spain}}\n* {{Official website|url=http://www.davidvilla7.es/en/}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/staff/players/villa/biography |title=FC Barcelona profile (fcbarcelona.com) |access-date=10 November 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111105172607/http://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/staff/players/villa/biography |archive-date=5 November 2011 |url-status=bot: unknown}}\n* {{BDFutbol|554}}\n* [http://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/j554.html?cat=SEL National team data] at BDFutbol\n* {{ESPN FC|28600}}\n* [http://www.campusdavidvilla.com/ The David Villa Campus official website] {{in lang|es}}\n* {{Cite web |url=http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/southafrica2010/players/player%3D229884/index.html |title=2010 FIFA World Cup profile (fifa.com) |access-date=3 May 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101207071127/http://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/southafrica2010/players/player%3D229884/index.html |archive-date=7 December 2010 |url-status=bot: unknown}}\n* {{MLS player|david-villa}}\n* {{NFT player|9992}}\n* {{FIFA player|229884}}\n* {{UEFA player|66414}}\n*{{J.League player}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title = Spain squads\n| bg        = #C60B1E\n| fg        = #FBEA0E\n| bordercolor = #000033\n|list1 =\n{{Spain squad 2006 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad UEFA Euro 2008}}\n{{Spain squad 2009 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2013 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n{{Spain squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title = Awards\n|bg = Gold\n|fg = Navy\n|list1 =\n{{UEFA Euro 2008 Team of the Tournament}}\n{{2009 FIFA Confederations Cup Team of the Tournament}}\n{{2010 FIFA World Cup Team of the Tournament}}\n{{2010 UEFA Team of the Year}}\n{{UEFA European Football Championship top scorers}}\n{{FIFA World Cup Bronze Ball}}\n{{Sporting de Gij\u00f3n Player of the Season}}\n{{ESPY Best MLS Player}}\n{{La Lig